The paper deals with the performance analysis of indoor Terahertz (THz) communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of array-of-subarrays architecture and hybrid precoding involves multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) techniques, which are also relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the closed-form expression of the achievable rate, which is related to system modeling and control (cs.SY).
